Hi everyone

We released Hotfix 3.6.2 that changes `core_validator` and will require a bittensor update of all validators.
If you run `core_validator` please update your bittensor installation as soon as you can, otherwise your validator runs the risk of going out-of-consensus which will negatively affect its dividends.

**Background**:
The previous validator robustness update had the purpose of eliminating clusters of servers that are overfit to the validation data, but actually have poor generalization performance. We introduced a logits divergence statistic as anomaly detector, which measures the divergence of server responses to the overall network response, and the weights get penalized to the degree that it diverges beyond two standard deviations (in the ~2% most extreme of responses).

At the time we deemed the risk of penalty to normal models to be low, based on testing on smaller models, but after reviewing its recent operation in nakamoto we have found the anomaly detection to be too sensitive. As this is a divergence measure relative to the network itself, and with the network predominantly hosting ~2.7B parameter models, it skewed statistics used in the anomaly detection such that it negatively impacts larger models.

This latest hotfix introduces subtensor hyperparameters to enable on-demand control of context pruning and the logits divergence penalty, with the goal of promoting accurate generalization measurement under changing network conditions. Note that we will attempt to optimize these hyperparameters over the next couple of weeks, and that it'll take a few days for new changes to take effect on the scoring due to the exponential moving average at the validators.

[Hotfix 3.6.2] **Validator robustness amendments**:
- Adds `ValidatorPruneLen` subtensor hyperparameter (current value is 1 token pruned randomly), that controls the amount of context pruning to assist in more accurate generalization measurement.
- Adds `ValidatorLogitsDivergence` subtensor hyperparameter (current value is 0.5, down from 1 before), that controls the penalty factor in [0, 1] that scales the logits divergence excess penalty, allowing the penalty to be reduced or turned off. The new value halves the current penalty, with a further series of reductions planned, provisionally 0.3 early next week, then 0.1 later next week, with possible further reductions thereafter. This serves as the announcement of further reductions in the next couple of weeks, although we'll obtain feedback from the community in #mining and report irregular findings.
- During each `core_validator` epoch these two hyperparams are updated from subtensor, which allows for uniform changes across all validators when generalization strategies involving context pruning and logits divergence excess need to be revised.

**Resources generated**:
  - github: https://github.com/opentensor/bittensor/releases/tag/v3.6.2
  - pypi: https://pypi.org/project/bittensor/3.6.2/
  - docker: https://hub.docker.com/r/opentensorfdn/bittensor/tags?page=1&name=3.6.2

Kind regards,
